== 2. Nc3 ==
This is a flexible alternative move order in the Caro-Kann, where White has not committed the pawn to d4 yet.

After [[/2...d5|'''2...d5''']] (near enough the only move, contesting the centre as Black prepared to do on move one), White may still play 3. d4 and transpose into the more common 2. d4 & 3. Nc3 Caro-Kann. However, the plan usually is to play 3. Nf3, the two knights attack. 3. Qf3 is the unusual Goldman variation. 

